                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d918">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.008 North Pacific/214: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-24T17:00:00+09:00"
                            >November 24, 1937—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 24—7:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>563. Department’s 311, November 22, 7 p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>I called today on the Minister for Foreign Affairs and after a long oral
                        explanation of the salmon fisheries situation in which the urgency of the
                        matter was especially emphasized, I left with him the memorandum and <hi
                            rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi>. The Minister made no comment except to
                        express surprise that Japanese were still fishing for salmon in Alaskan
                        waters in spite of the refusal of the Government to grant licenses. He said
                        that he would immediately take the matter up with the Department of
                        Agriculture and would give us a reply at the earliest possible
                        moment.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>No opportunity occurred to bring up the substance of paragraph 4 of the
                        Department’s 308.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
